<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 18 at 12:08AM CST  by NWS Mobile</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southern Crenshaw and
Covington Counties through 1245 AM CST...
At 1208 AM CST, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated
strong thunderstorms along a line extending from 3 miles west of
Dozier to 13 miles southwest of Andalusia. Movement was east at 40
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Andalusia, Opp, Brantley, River Falls, Red Level, Dozier, Heath and
Gantt.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
